<Layout
  title="GOSIM Open-Source AI Strategy Forum"
  description="GOSIM Open-Source AI Strategy Forum - GOSIM Paris, the City of Light, transforms into the City of Artificial Brilliance this May. GOSIM AI 2025 invites visionaries, disruptors, and pioneers to converge at Station F, a crucible of innovation, to shape the next frontier of AI."
  navDarkMode={true}
  navBackground="header-home"
  pageTransitionName="GOSIM Open-Source AI Strategy Forum"
>
  <ForumHero description="Co-organized By the Eclipse Foundation" date="May 5, 2025" location="Invitation Only" links={[]} />
  <div
    class="section-wrap"
    id="intro"
    data-theme-section="light"
    data-bg-section="lightgray"
  >
    <Intro>
      <h1
        class="h3 light split-words animate-read mb-4"
        style="font-size:1.5rem; text-align: justify;"
      >
        Co-organized by the <b
          ><a
            href="https://www.eclipse.org/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer">Eclipse Foundation</a
          ></b
        > and <b
          ><a
            href="https://gosim.org/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer">GOSIM</a
          ></b
        >, the Open Source AI Strategy Forum brings together global thought
        leaders, researchers, and open-source AI pioneers, and digital
        sovereignty advocates to reflect on the strategic role of open source AI
        in global collaboration and the pressing challenges we are facing. The
        Forum adopts a hybrid format with short presentations and a priority on
        open dialogue and collective thinking, operating under the <b
          ><a
            href="https://www.chathamhouse.org/about-us/chatham-house-rule"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer">Chatham House Rule</a
          ></b
        > to ensure that all participants can freely exchange ideas. The event will
        culminate in a networking dinner cruise along the Seine River, providing
        a scenic and informal setting for further discussions and collaborations.
      </h1>
    </Intro>
  </div>

